Rosemary is a plant which can be used in different ways as an aromatic medicinal and as a
culinary plant. Accordingly, it is grown all over the world, particularly in Spain, France, England,
Russia and Portugal. This genus is extremely rich in essential oil, although there are large intraspecies
differences in terms of the yield and quality of the essential oil produced.
